# 01 — Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)

## Overview

This folder contains the complete 20-step dataset discovery and 
data profiling notebook for the Retail AI Intelligence Platform project.
It was the first phase of the project — understanding the data deeply 
before building anything.

## File

| File        | Description                                 |
|-------------|---------------------------------------------|
| `EDA.ipynb` | Complete EDA notebook — run in Google Colab |

## How to Run

1. Open [Google Colab](https://colab.research.google.com)
2. Upload `EDA.ipynb`
3. Upload all 6 CSV files to the Colab session:
   - `Customers.csv`
   - `Products.csv`
   - `Sales.csv`
   - `Stores.csv`
   - `Exchange_Rates.csv`
   - `Data_Dictionary.csv`
4. Run all cells in order (`Runtime → Run all`)

## What the Notebook Does

The notebook covers 20 steps across 3 main areas:

### Dataset Discovery
- Step 1 — Load all 6 CSV files with automatic encoding detection
- Step 2 — Column-level analysis (nulls, uniques, dtypes, suspicious values)
- Step 3 — Business interpretation of every table
- Step 4 — Primary key detection
- Step 5 — Foreign key and relationship detection
- Step 6 — ER diagram generation (text + Mermaid)
- Step 7 — Full data quality audit (HIGH / MEDIUM / LOW severity)

### Business Analysis
- Step 8 — Time analysis and seasonality detection
- Step 9 — Sales deep analysis with YoY growth
- Step 10 — Customer demographics and segmentation
- Step 11 — Product analysis and price distribution
- Step 12 — Store performance analysis
- Step 13 — Exchange rate trends and FX strategy

### Architecture Planning
- Step 14 — Feature engineering ideas
- Step 15 — dbt modelling architecture plan
- Step 16 — Power BI dashboard blueprint
- Step 17 — KPI catalogue
- Step 18 — DAX measure suggestions
- Step 19 — Final professional summary report
- Step 20 — Bonus: correlation analysis, outlier detection, RFM framework

## Key Findings

| Metric                     | Value                                                         |
|----------------------------|---------------------------------------------------------------|
| Total Transactions         | 62,884                                                        |
| Countries                  | 8                                                             |
| Currencies                 | 5 (USD, CAD, AUD, EUR, GBP)                                   |
| Date Range                 | 2016 – 2021                                                   |
| Total Revenue (list price) | $55.7M                                                        |
| Avg Gross Margin           | 54.9%                                                         |
| FK Integrity               | Zero orphan records across all 3 relationships                |
| Data Quality Issues        | 1 HIGH (Delivery Date 79.1% null — by design, online channel) |
| Inactive Customers         | 3,379 (22.1% of total base)                                   |
| Pareto Finding             | Top 20% of SKUs drive 70% of revenue                          |

## Dependencies

```python
pandas
numpy
matplotlib
seaborn
```

All pre-installed in Google Colab — no additional setup needed.

## Output

Running this notebook produces:

- Dataset overview table with memory and encoding info
- Column profiles for all 6 tables
- FK relationship audit with match percentages
- Data quality severity rankings
- Sales trend charts (monthly, annual, category)
- Customer demographic charts
- Product margin and distribution charts
- Store performance charts
- Exchange rate trend charts
- Seasonality heatmap
- Revenue outlier boxplot
- Complete architecture planning for dbt and Power BI
